OL,3,CMore than 20 otter cubs rescued after
OL,4,Cflooded rivers wash their homes away
OL,6,FOtters mainly feed on fish -
OL,7,Fparticularly eels and salmonids -
OL,8,Fwaterbirds, amphibians and crustaceans.
OL,10,FThey have their cubs in underground
OL,11,Fburrows, known as "holts", and the
OL,12,Fyoung are swimming in the water by 10
OL,13,Fweeks of age.
OL,15,FMr Webb explained that, while a few
OL,16,Ffamilies manage to reunite after the
OL,17,Ffloods subside, many do not, and some
OL,18,Fof the cubs rescued in March were
OL,19,Ffound alone on a riverbank.
