OL,3,CMore than 20 otter cubs rescued after
OL,4,Cflooded rivers wash their homes away
OL,6,FHe added that, in the South West,
OL,7,Fotters typically tended to be rescued
OL,8,Ffrom the Tor and Fowey floodplains.
OL,10,F"But every river will have this
OL,11,Fproblem at some point, and it's
OL,12,Fsomething we shouldn't be complacent
OL,13,Fabout.
OL,15,F"Otters are known for being very
OL,16,Fadaptable, but living with fast-
OL,17,Fflowing water all the time can be
OL,18,Fproblem.
