OL,3,CMore than 20 otter cubs rescued after
OL,4,Cflooded rivers wash their homes away
OL,6,F"Their natural home is the rivers and
OL,7,Fif it's continually under water
OL,8,Fthey're going to move inland to
OL,9,Ffishing lakes. The young will drown
OL,10,Fand the reproduction rate will suffer.
OL,12,F"Pollution in the rivers doesn't help
OL,13,Feither, combined with flash flooding,
OL,14,Fit's a recipe for disaster in my
OL,15,Feyes," Mr Webb said.
